    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1928-03-13T17:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1928-03-13T17:00:00-05:00" n="208"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d208">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">500.A15/663: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the Chief
                        of the American Representation on the Preparatory Commission</hi> (<persName
                        type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Gibson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1928-03-13T17:00:00-05:00">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 13, 1928—5 p.m.</hi>
                        </date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>3. Your telegram No. 5 of March 12. I particularly desire that the questions you
                    suggest should not be answered in Geneva. These are <pb facs="0377" n="249"
                        xml:id="pg_249"/> questions which have place only as between the parties
                    concerned in direct negotiations for the concluding of a treaty. There is no
                    reason why the nations represented in the Preparatory Commission should inquire
                    into the meaning or language of a treaty proposed by France to the United
                    States, and which is still being discussed. If you are asked any such questions,
                    you should state that the party in question should take up negotiations on the
                    matter in Washington.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Kellogg</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
